entry.content: Data released by the Australian Bureau of Statistics has found 7% of patients who needed to see a GP did not see a doctor or delayed booking an appointment due to the cost in 2022-23, a percentage that has doubled from 2021-22. One in five people said the cost was the reason for delaying or not seeking mental health support when needed, and one in 10 said cost was the reason for not seeing a specialist. #australia #abs #costofliving #news #australiannews #learnontiktok #todayilearned #statistics #2023
